# Premium Login Page Redesign

I have completely redesigned the login page to use a modern "Double Slider" animation. When switching between "Sign In" and "Sign Up", the overlay panel slides across the screen to reveal the alternate form.

## Changes

### 1. CSS ([Frontend/src/styles.css](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/styles.css))
-   Replaced the old static grid/flex styles for `.login-container`.
-   Added `.auth-container`, `.overlay-container`, `.sign-in-container`, `.sign-up-container` classes.
-   Implemented CSS transitions (`transform: translateX(...)`) for the smooth sliding effect.

### 2. React Component ([Frontend/src/pages/Auth/LoginPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/pages/Auth/LoginPage.jsx))
-   Overhauled the HTML structure to match the sliding design pattern.
-   The state `isRegister` now toggles the `right-panel-active` class on the main container, which triggers the CSS animations.
-   **Preserved Logic**: The API calls for [handleLogin](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/pages/Auth/LoginPage.jsx#20-61) and [handleRegister](file:///c:/Users/HPPAVILION/Documents/Cusor/Cafe_app/my-app/Frontend/src/pages/Auth/LoginPage.jsx#71-114) are exactly the same, ensuring backend integration remains working.

